{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-18",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_18_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fall Guy",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 8,
  "page_start_sec": 746.016,
  "page_end_sec": 988.48,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.553,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 746.016,
      "end": 747.08,
      "text": "There's no way out of it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 747.552,
      "end": 748.46,
      "text": "Let's give them the punk."
    },
    {
      "start": 749.26,
      "end": 751.18,
      "text": "He nodded pleasantly at the boy in the doorway.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 751.98,
      "end": 753.66,
      "text": "He actually did shoot both of them,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 753.74,
      "end": 754.82,
      "text": "Thursby and Jacoby,"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.92,
      "end": 755.36,
      "text": "didn't he?"
    },
    {
      "start": 755.87,
      "end": 756.42,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 756.6,
      "end": 758.08,
      "text": "he's made to order for the part."
    },
    {
      "start": 758.784,
      "end": 761.5,
      "text": "Let's pin the necessary evidence on him and turn him over to them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 762.64,
      "end": 764.56,
      "text": "The boy in the doorway tightened the corners of",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 764.56,
      "end": 767.18,
      "text": "his mouth in what may have been a minute smile."
    },
    {
      "start": 768.416,
      "end": 771.06,
      "text": "Spade's proposal seemed to have no other effect on him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 771.808,
      "end": 774.26,
      "text": "Joel Cairo's dark face was open-mouthed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 774.56,
      "end": 774.98,
      "text": "open-eyed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 775.16,
      "end": 775.82,
      "text": "yellowish,"
    },
    {
      "start": 775.84,
      "end": 776.28,
      "text": "and amazed."
    },
    {
      "start": 777.22,
      "end": 778.28,
      "text": "He breathed through his mouth,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 778.64,
      "end": 779.08,
      "text": "his round,"
    },
    {
      "start": 779.22,
      "end": 780.92,
      "text": "effeminate chest rising and falling,"
    },
    {
      "start": 781.4,
      "end": 782.52,
      "text": "while he gaped at Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 783.488,
      "end": 785.64,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy had moved away from Spade",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 785.64,
      "end": 788.02,
      "text": "and had twisted herself around on the sofa to"
    },
    {
      "start": 788.02,
      "end": 788.68,
      "text": "stare at him."
    },
    {
      "start": 788.86,
      "end": 791.2,
      "text": "There was a suggestion of hysterical"
    },
    {
      "start": 791.2,
      "end": 793.7,
      "text": "laughter behind the startled confusion in her"
    },
    {
      "start": 793.78,
      "end": 794.0,
      "text": "face."
    },
    {
      "start": 794.976,
      "end": 797.68,
      "text": "Gutman remained still and expressionless for a long moment.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 798.22,
      "end": 799.42,
      "text": "Then he decided to laugh."
    },
    {
      "start": 800.12,
      "end": 802.0,
      "text": "He laughed heartily and lengthily,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 802.08,
      "end": 804.68,
      "text": "but not stopping until his sleek eyes had borrowed"
    },
    {
      "start": 804.82,
      "end": 806.02,
      "text": "merriment from his laughter."
    },
    {
      "start": 807.1,
      "end": 807.96,
      "text": "When he stopped laughing,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 808.02,
      "end": 808.38,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.66,
      "end": 809.36,
      "text": "By gad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 809.54,
      "end": 809.74,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 810.0,
      "end": 811.12,
      "text": "you're a character,"
    },
    {
      "start": 811.52,
      "end": 812.12,
      "text": "that you are."
    },
    {
      "start": 812.49,
      "end": 815.18,
      "text": "He took a white handkerchief from his pocket and"
    },
    {
      "start": 815.26,
      "end": 815.94,
      "text": "wiped his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 816.3,
      "end": 816.94,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 816.94,
      "end": 817.2,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 817.32,
      "end": 820.04,
      "text": "there's never any telling what you'll do or say next,"
    },
    {
      "start": 820.24,
      "end": 821.26,
      "text": "except that it's bound"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.26,
      "end": 822.32,
      "text": "to be something astonishing."
    },
    {
      "start": 823.616,
      "end": 824.88,
      "text": "There's nothing funny about it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 825.44,
      "end": 827.1,
      "text": "Spade did not seem offended by the fat",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 827.16,
      "end": 827.72,
      "text": "man's laughter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.88,
      "end": 829.28,
      "text": "nor in any way impressed."
    },
    {
      "start": 830.16,
      "end": 832.85,
      "text": "He spoke in the manner of one reasoning with a recalcitrant",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 833.2,
      "end": 835.14,
      "text": "but not altogether unreasonable friend."
    },
    {
      "start": 835.45,
      "end": 836.88,
      "text": "It's our best bet."
    },
    {
      "start": 837.56,
      "end": 838.36,
      "text": "With him in their hands,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 838.5,
      "end": 839.12,
      "text": "the police will."
    },
    {
      "start": 840.0,
      "end": 840.88,
      "text": "But my dear man,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 841.16,
      "end": 842.1,
      "text": "Gutman objected,"
    },
    {
      "start": 842.1,
      "end": 842.76,
      "text": "can't you see?"
    },
    {
      "start": 843.5,
      "end": 845.66,
      "text": "If I even for a moment thought of doing it?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 845.92,
      "end": 847.6,
      "text": "But that's ridiculous too."
    },
    {
      "start": 847.84,
      "end": 850.22,
      "text": "I feel towards Wilmer just exactly"
    },
    {
      "start": 850.8,
      "end": 852.14,
      "text": "as if he were my own son.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 852.28,
      "end": 852.86,
      "text": "I really"
    },
    {
      "start": 852.94,
      "end": 853.14,
      "text": "do."
    },
    {
      "start": 854.08,
      "end": 856.7,
      "text": "But if I even for a moment thought of doing what you propose,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 857.44,
      "end": 858.72,
      "text": "what in the world do you think",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 858.9,
      "end": 861.12,
      "text": "would keep Wilmer from telling the police every"
    },
    {
      "start": 861.12,
      "end": 864.06,
      "text": "last detail about the Falcon and all of us."
    },
    {
      "start": 864.896,
      "end": 866.2,
      "text": "Spade grinned with stiff lips.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 866.9,
      "end": 867.52,
      "text": "If we had to,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 867.6,
      "end": 868.22,
      "text": "he said softly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 868.42,
      "end": 869.86,
      "text": "we could have him killed resisting"
    },
    {
      "start": 870.0,
      "end": 870.36,
      "text": "arrest."
    },
    {
      "start": 871.3,
      "end": 872.6,
      "text": "But we won't have to go that far.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 873.26,
      "end": 874.26,
      "text": "Let him talk his head off.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 874.72,
      "end": 876.12,
      "text": "I promise you nobody will do"
    },
    {
      "start": 876.26,
      "end": 877.02,
      "text": "anything about it."
    },
    {
      "start": 877.536,
      "end": 878.9,
      "text": "That's easy enough to fix."
    },
    {
      "start": 879.34,
      "end": 882.42,
      "text": "The pink flesh on Gutman's forehead crawled in a frown."
    },
    {
      "start": 882.6,
      "end": 883.98,
      "text": "He lowered his head,"
    },
    {
      "start": 884.02,
      "end": 886.74,
      "text": "mashing his chins together over his collar and asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 886.92,
      "end": 887.4,
      "text": "How?"
    },
    {
      "start": 888.17,
      "end": 888.82,
      "text": "Then,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 888.96,
      "end": 891.96,
      "text": "with an abruptness that set all his fat bulbs to quivering"
    },
    {
      "start": 892.18,
      "end": 893.88,
      "text": "and tumbling against one another,"
    },
    {
      "start": 894.06,
      "end": 895.32,
      "text": "he raised his head,"
    },
    {
      "start": 895.968,
      "end": 898.56,
      "text": "squirmed around to look at the boy and laughed uproariously.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 899.4,
      "end": 900.26,
      "text": "What do you think of this,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 900.34,
      "end": 900.58,
      "text": "Wilmer?"
    },
    {
      "start": 901.408,
      "end": 901.82,
      "text": "It's funny,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 901.92,
      "end": 902.06,
      "text": "eh?"
    },
    {
      "start": 903.2,
      "end": 906.08,
      "text": "The boy's eyes were cold hazel gleams under his lashes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 906.48,
      "end": 907.5,
      "text": "He said in a low,"
    },
    {
      "start": 907.54,
      "end": 908.24,
      "text": "distinct voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 908.7,
      "end": 909.3,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 909.38,
      "end": 910.12,
      "text": "it's funny,"
    },
    {
      "start": 910.28,
      "end": 911.46,
      "text": "the son of a bitch."
    },
    {
      "start": 912.416,
      "end": 914.3,
      "text": "Spade was talking to Bridget O'Shaughnessy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 914.8,
      "end": 915.78,
      "text": "How do you feel now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 915.92,
      "end": 916.2,
      "text": "Angel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 916.42,
      "end": 917.04,
      "text": "Any better?"
    },
    {
      "start": 917.66,
      "end": 918.2,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 918.42,
      "end": 919.18,
      "text": "much better,"
    },
    {
      "start": 919.26,
      "end": 919.88,
      "text": "only..."
    },
    {
      "start": 920.32,
      "end": 922.52,
      "text": "She reduced her voice until the last words"
    },
    {
      "start": 922.52,
      "end": 925.04,
      "text": "would have been unintelligible two feet away."
    },
    {
      "start": 925.984,
      "end": 926.46,
      "text": "I'm frightened.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 927.68,
      "end": 927.98,
      "text": "Don't be,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 928.32,
      "end": 929.12,
      "text": "he said carelessly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 929.3,
      "end": 931.68,
      "text": "and put a hand on her gray stockinged knee."
    },
    {
      "start": 932.64,
      "end": 934.18,
      "text": "Nothing very bad's going to happen.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 934.72,
      "end": 935.2,
      "text": "Want a drink?"
    },
    {
      "start": 936.28,
      "end": 936.58,
      "text": "Not now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 936.74,
      "end": 937.0,
      "text": "thanks."
    },
    {
      "start": 937.28,
      "end": 938.52,
      "text": "Her voice sank again."
    },
    {
      "start": 939.4,
      "end": 939.78,
      "text": "Be careful,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 939.88,
      "end": 940.04,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 940.85,
      "end": 942.52,
      "text": "Spade grinned and looked at Gutman,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 942.7,
      "end": 943.84,
      "text": "who was looking at him."
    },
    {
      "start": 944.38,
      "end": 946.0,
      "text": "The fat man smiled genially,"
    },
    {
      "start": 946.26,
      "end": 947.64,
      "text": "saying nothing for a moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 947.68,
      "end": 948.32,
      "text": "and then asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 948.86,
      "end": 948.98,
      "text": "How?"
    },
    {
      "start": 950.176,
      "end": 950.94,
      "text": "Spade was stupid.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 951.7,
      "end": 952.1,
      "text": "How what?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 953.22,
      "end": 955.76,
      "text": "The fat man considered more laughter necessary then,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 955.9,
      "end": 957.02,
      "text": "and an explanation."
    },
    {
      "start": 957.94,
      "end": 958.18,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 958.18,
      "end": 958.4,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 958.56,
      "end": 960.52,
      "text": "if you're really serious about this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 960.96,
      "end": 962.1,
      "text": "the suggestion of yours,"
    },
    {
      "start": 962.8,
      "end": 965.74,
      "text": "the least we can do in common politeness is to hear you out.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 966.7,
      "end": 969.22,
      "text": "Now how are you going about fixing it so that Wilmer,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 969.44,
      "end": 971.14,
      "text": "he paused here to laugh again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 971.44,
      "end": 973.6,
      "text": "won't be able to do us any harm."
    },
    {
      "start": 974.752,
      "end": 975.68,
      "text": "Spade shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 976.02,
      "end": 976.54,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 976.7,
      "end": 977.14,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 977.52,
      "end": 980.36,
      "text": "I wouldn't want to take advantage of anybody's politeness,"
    },
    {
      "start": 980.42,
      "end": 982.0,
      "text": "no matter how common like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 982.52,
      "end": 982.88,
      "text": "Forget it."
    },
    {
      "start": 983.12,
      "end": 986.0,
      "text": "The fat man puckered up his facial bulbs."
    },
    {
      "start": 986.78,
      "end": 987.2,
      "text": "Now come,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 987.32,
      "end": 987.52,
      "text": "come,"
    },
    {
      "start": 987.64,
      "end": 988.48,
      "text": "he protested."
    }
  ]
}